The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases worldwide has surpassed 309 million, with over 5.4 million deaths, the latest data from Johns Hopkins University shows. Here is the latest: The Chinese mainland recorded 192 confirmed COVID-19 cases on Monday, with 110 linked to local transmissions and 82 from overseas. Philippine Interior Secretary Eduardo Ano said on Tuesday that he has tested positive for COVID-19. The Southeast Asian country reported 33,169 new COVID-19 infections on Monday, a new record daily spike. The country has recorded nearly 3 million confirmed cases so far, with 52,293 deaths.